OL,3,CTories to amend Equality Act to make
OL,4,C'biological sex' protected
OL,5,Ccharacteristic
OL,7,FThe Tories say that Labour's Equality
OL,8,FAct has not kept pace with evolving
OL,9,Finterpretations and is not
OL,10,Fsufficiently clear on when it means
OL,11,Fsex and when it means gender.
OL,13,FThe party says the proposed change to
OL,14,Fthe law will not remove the existing
OL,15,Fand continuing protections against
OL,16,Fdiscrimination on the basis of gender
OL,17,Freassignment provided by the Equality
OL,18,FAct.
