OL,3,CTories to amend Equality Act to make
OL,4,C'biological sex' protected
OL,5,Ccharacteristic
OL,7,FThe sex of those with a Gender
OL,8,FRecognition Certificate will still
OL,9,Falign with their acquired gender in
OL,10,Flaw outside the Equality Act, for
OL,11,Fexample marriage law, as is the status
OL,12,Fquo.
OL,14,FUnder the new scheme the Conservatives
OL,15,Fwill also establish in law that gender
OL,16,Frecognition is a reserved matter, with
OL,17,Fwomen and equalities minister Kemi
OL,18,FBadenoch saying, "it is impracticable
OL,19,Ffor gender recognition regimes to vary
OL,20,Fin different parts of the country".
