OL,3,CTories to amend Equality Act to make
OL,4,C'biological sex' protected
OL,5,Ccharacteristic
OL,7,F"That is why we are today pledging
OL,8,Fthat, if we form a government after
OL,9,Fthe election, we will clarify that sex
OL,10,Fin the law means biological sex and
OL,11,Fnot new, redefined meanings of the
OL,12,Fword."
OL,14,FWriting in The Times, Ms Badenoch gave
OL,15,Ffurther detail on what the proposed
OL,16,Fchanges would mean, and attacked
OL,17,FLabour leader Sir Keir Starmer for
OL,18,Fgoing "round in circles" on the issue.
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@FO]zD@GOUzD@XO]
