OL,7,FMs Badenoch wrote: "We are one United
OL,8,FKingdom and it is impracticable for
OL,9,Fgender recognition regimes to vary in
OL,10,Fdifferent parts of the country. So, we
OL,11,Fwill also legislate to establish that
OL,12,Fgender recognition is a reserved
OL,13,Fmatter.
OL,15,F"On fundamental matters of personal
OL,16,Fidentity there should be one approach
OL,17,Fthroughout the United Kingdom."
